					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">PH5 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I will check on the scrolling, from what I have seen, that seems likely.  Is it a quirk of the machine that the scrolling needs to be reset all the time?</div>
<br />The VRAM read/write port (PPUADDR/PPUDATA, $2006/$2007) uses the same register inside the PPU as the scroll position (PPUSCROLL, $2005). So yes, after you upload new data to the PPU, you need to reset the scroll position.</div>

